- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper presents a polynomial time algorithm. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is relevant as the paper discusses well-ordering and ordinals. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is possible as the lexicographic order is used in the paper. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with the complexity of determining well-ordering of languages.
